cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically sentiment analysis, in code-mixed Hindi-English texts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related tasks. The paper also uses deep learning methods, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper deals with enhancing model performance, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions lack of well-learnt representations, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with text analysis, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
